function lonlat = mapcoords(v)%Function LONLAT = MAPCOORDS(V) -- Create vector of map coordinates.%  Uses WHOI's WORLDMAP to create a coastline map for a sector of the%  world defined by V = [minlon,maxlon,minlat,maxlat], where longitudes%  are given in degrees east of Greenwich. Then the user can mouse-click%  at selected points that are echoed back onto the map and written %  to a file called LONLAT = [lon,lat]. MAPCOORDS returns control to%  the command window after detecting a mouse-click to right of the plot%  frame of the map. NOTE: If the domain defined by V straddles the %  Greenwich meridian, east longitudes can be expressed as degrees %  greater than 360. E.g., V=[260 390 -60 65] defines a region from%  100W eastward to 30E and from 60S to 65N. %%  Written by D.B. Enfield, November, 1995%  NOAA/Atlantic Oceanographic & Meteorological Laboratory%  Miami, FL 33149 (305-361-4351); enfield@aoml.noaa.govclf;figure(1);x=.5*(v(1)+v(2));worldmap(v);hold onwhile x<v(2)	[x,y]=ginput(1);	lonlat=[lonlat' [x;y]]';	plot(x,y,'oc','EraseMode','none')endplot(x,y,'ok','EraseMode','none')nn=length(lonlat(:,1));lonlat(nn,:)=[];hold off